# Phase 10: Advanced Community & Studio Features

## Goal Description
Implement real community features and a creator studio dashboard. This includes a new `posts` table for community updates and a studio page for managing uploaded videos.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Schema
#### [NEW] [setup-community.sql](file:///C:/GoLive/setup-community.sql)
- Create `posts` table (id, user_id, content, image_url, likes_count, created_at).
- Add RLS policies for posts (public read, owner write).

### Community Features
#### [MODIFY] [CommunityTab.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/components/CommunityTab.tsx)
- Connect to Supabase `posts` table.
- Implement "Create Post" functionality for channel owners.
- Display real posts feed.

### Creator Studio
#### [NEW] [app/studio/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/studio/page.tsx)
- A dashboard for creators to manage their content.
- List all videos uploaded by the current user.
- Add "Delete Video" functionality.
- Show analytics summary (total views, likes).

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Build verification (`npm run build`).

### Manual Verification
- **Community**: Post a status update as a logged-in user, verify it appears in the feed.
- **Studio**: Go to `/studio`, see list of videos, delete a test video, verify it's gone.
